\f0\fs24 Finally, Jonathan reached for his own weapon. He\'92d tucked his pistol into the back of his trousers, beneath the small of his back so it was concealed under his shirt. He reached for it with deft hands, but Connor\'92s killer was quicker. Much quicker.\
\'93Drop it,\'94 said the killer, already on his feet. His voice was cold, threatening. He had already killed Connor, and Jonathan was now the sole witness. It {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://424527F9-F7A6-4AF5-B749-513CCF0862E3"}}{\fldrslt seemed}} unlikely that he would hesitate to shoot Jonathan now. He hesitated to relinquish his weapon, but he had little choice but to do as the killer asked. Taking care not to make any sudden moves, he set the gun on the floor.\
\'93Kick it over here.\'94
